					<head>Kabbalah</head>
					<msContents class="lccn.loc.gov/sh85018546" rend="visible">
						<summary>Kabbalistic writings of Shelomoh ben David ha-Kohen.</summary>
						<textLang mainLang="he" otherLangs="jrb"/>
						<msItem rend="">
							<locus from="1r" to="168v"/>
							<title xml:lang="he-Latn-x-lc">Leḥem Shelomoh</title>
							<title xml:lang="he">לחם שלמה</title>
							<note>
								<p>The text is based on several kabbalistic works, e.g., Tolaʿat Yaʿaḳov, Maʿarekhet ha-elohut, Shaʿare orah, Derekh emunah and Sefer kaṿanot. </p>
								<p>Folios 1 and 2 contain a piece, incomplete at the end, etitled Seder kol ha-nimtsa᾿im (on the order of worlds). </p>
								<p>Appended are: Sha῾are yedi῾at ha-midot ṿeha-mishḳalot (Arabic in Hebrew characters, imperfect at the end), folios 167r-167v; an incomplete list of passages from Tana"kh and Mishnah, folio 168r.</p>
								<p>See further <ref target="Kiryat_Sefer" type="number">28</ref> (1953), pp. 396-397 no. 177.</p>
							</note>
							<author>
								<persName xml:lang="en" key="http://viaf.org/viaf/293149006">Shelomoh ben David, ha-Kohen</persName>
								<persName xml:lang="he" key="http://viaf.org/viaf/293149006">שלמה בן דוד, הכהן</persName>
							</author>
						</msItem>
					</msContents>
					<physDesc rend="visible">
						<p>Paper codex of the second half of the 17th century.</p>
						<objectDesc form="codex">
							<supportDesc material="chart">
								<support>Paper.</support>
								<extent>168 folios<dimensions type="leaf" unit="mm">
										<height>152</height>
										<width>95</width>
									</dimensions>
									<dimensions type="written" unit="mm">
										<height>125</height>
										<width>80</width>
									</dimensions>
								</extent>
								<foliation>
									<p>168 folios (+ 3 unfoliated paper flyleaf at the beginning and 4 at the end). </p>
									<p>Original Hebrew foliation is only partly preserved.</p>
								</foliation>
								<collation>
									<p>Quires of 8 leaves each.</p>
								</collation>
								<condition>
									<p>Leaves missing after folios 2, 9, 121, 167.</p>
									<p>Well-fingered, with dirt and grease in margins, especially lower corner – a few of the latter have been infilled.
</p>
									<p>A few tidemarks at head.
</p>
									<p>Paper slightly soft and weak from use.
</p>
									<p>Folio 168 has small loss at foredge.</p>
								</condition>
							</supportDesc>
							<layoutDesc>
								<layout columns="1 " ruledLines="16 22" writtenLines="16 22">
									<p>Uniform layout.</p>
									<p>Titles and initial words in larger square characters.</p>
									<p>Catchwords on every verso.</p>
									<p>Visible ruling.</p>
									<p>Running titles.</p>
								</layout>
							</layoutDesc>
						</objectDesc>
						<handDesc hands="2">
							<summary>Yemenite semi-cursive script of the second half of the 17th century. <name type="person" role="scribe">Shemarya ben Yosef ben Shalom</name>: inscribed, folio 166v (acrostic in the upper part of the page).</summary>
							<handNote script="Hebrew" scope="major"/>
						</handDesc>
						<additions>
							<p>A record of deposition of the manuscript, which was transferred  from Yehudah ῾Amar (?) to Yaakov ibn Daud Yosef, dated <date calendar="Seleucid">2026</date> (<date calendar="Gregorian">1715</date>), witnessed by Shemarya ben Yosef and Mosheh ibn Se῾adyah: inscribed in Arabic (in Hebrew characters), folio 20v.</p>
							<p>An entry with a list of purchased books, dated <date calendar="Gregorian">1866</date>: folio 168v, in Arabic (in Hebrew characters).</p>
						</additions>
